                   <h1 style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</h1>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;<strong>Coming up...&nbsp;</strong></h1>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Poetry in the Afternoon&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Thursday,&nbsp;March 10th&nbsp; 2:30 - 3:30 pm</strong></h2>
<p>Join us for a sampling of poems read aloud.&nbsp; Bring your favourite poem to share with the group.&nbsp; A little something for everyone - dramatic, funny, romantic or silly poems to make you smile.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tea served - Everyone welcome.&nbsp; (content is mostly&nbsp;for adults though some children's poetry is occasionally included)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;"><strong>Author's Coffee Morning&nbsp;&nbsp; -&nbsp; &nbsp;Saturday, March 12th 10:30am</strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>The Friends of the Summerland Library invite local writers to a conversation about our new library and how it can serve your needs for research and writing.&nbsp; The session will include an overview of physical and digital library resources and an informal dialogue to share suggestions and ideas with other writers.&nbsp; Come for coffee - in the Meeting Place.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong></strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src="assets/images/Image%20Bank%20for%20Branch%20Use/theatre.jpg" alt="" width="175" height="192" />&nbsp;</p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;<strong>"Four Minutes of Fame"...&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></h1>
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Saturday, March 12&nbsp; &nbsp;7pm</h1>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Bring in your original writing:&nbsp; Poems, Flights of Fantasy, Think pieces</h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">and Literary brickbats to our Open Mic night.</h2>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">"Four Minutes of Fame" delves into the riches of our local culture.&nbsp;</h3>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Hone your presentation down to four minutes and dazzle a great audience!&nbsp;</h3>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;Enjoy a musical interlude, coffee, tea and cookies.&nbsp; Adults drop-in by donation to the FOSLS.</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><strong>Library Bookclub</strong></h2>
<p>The bookclub meets monthly during the&nbsp;winter and spring&nbsp;to discuss a wide variety of fiction, non-fiction and biography.&nbsp; The choices range from popular fiction to classics to Canadian selections.&nbsp;&nbsp; The fall session of the bookclub has concluded.&nbsp;</p>
<p>We will meet <strong>Saturday,&nbsp;March 19th&nbsp;&nbsp;at 11am to discuss "Road Ends"</strong> by&nbsp;Mary Lawson.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The spring reading list is available at the library desk.</p>
<h2><strong></strong>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2><strong>iPad Club&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Thursday, March 31st&nbsp; &nbsp;3 - 4:15pm</strong></h2>
<p>Bring your fully charged iPad or iPhone, Apple ID, and your Library card.&nbsp; Share what you know and learn some new tips.&nbsp; Staff will be on hand to help you learn to download e-books or online library resources but we regret specific technical issues cannot be addressed at this informal club meeting.&nbsp; Everyone welcome - Drop in.</p>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>Preschool Programs</h2>
<p>The winter session is underway but there are still a few spots left.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Storytime for 3 1/2 -5 year olds, Toddlertime for 2 &amp; 3 year olds (with an adult) and Rhymetime for babies 2 &amp; under (with an adult)<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Please call or drop in to the library to register for these free programs.</p>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>KNITTERS GROUP -&nbsp;</h2>
<h2><strong>Meets every Saturday afternoon in the Community Room 2 - 4pm&nbsp;</strong></h2>
<h3>Come share you latest project with other knitter's.&nbsp; Bring your own supplies, scan the shelves for new&nbsp; pattern books and make new friends.&nbsp; Refreshments served.</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>~BookChat and Crochet Club have concluded for the winter.&nbsp; These programs will resume in the fall.</h3>
<h3>&nbsp;</h3>
<h3>LIBRARY-AT-YOUR-DOOR</h3>
<p>This volunteer group has been active at the Summerland Library since 1999.&nbsp; Volunteers bring library materials to those that are homebound and cannot get into the library.&nbsp; If you are interested in joining this group of dedicated volunteers please ask at the circulation desk.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>&nbsp;THE FRIENDS OF THE SUMMERLAND LIBRARY</h3>
<h3>The Friends of the Summerland Library mission statement:</h3>
<p><em>&nbsp;"To encourage and support literacy for all</em>".&nbsp; The Friends of the Library&nbsp;advocate awareness of library services through their support of programs, presenting author visits&nbsp;and hands-on participation in literacy-based activities.&nbsp; The directors of the FOSLS meet the first Thursday each month downstairs in the library basement viewing room.&nbsp;</p>
<p>________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</p>
